According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Active Alignment Equipment Market was valued at USD 754 million in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 817 million in 2025 to USD 1.33 billion by 2031, registering a CAGR of 8.7% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing robust growth as manufacturers increasingly adopt precision alignment technologies to improve the performance of camera modules used in smartphones, advanced driver-assistance systems (ADAS), autonomous vehicles, medical imaging devices, and industrial vision systems. Continuous advancements in automation, artificial intelligence, and machine vision are enabling active alignment equipment to achieve sub-micron precision while improving manufacturing efficiency, making it an indispensable technology across modern imaging applications.
